.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH antimony-refresh 1  "refresh " 
.SH NAME
antimony\-refresh \- Refresh caches
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBantimony refresh\fR [\fB\-d\fR|\fB\-\-dry\fR] [\fB\-\-hard\fR] [\fB\-s\fR|\fB\-\-seccomp\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIPROFILE\fR] [\fIPASSTHROUGH\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Refresh caches
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-dry\fR
Just delete the cache, don\*(Aqt repopulate
.TP
\fB\-\-hard\fR
Delete the entire Cache directory. Will break any instance currently running!
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-seccomp\fR
Refresh the SECCOMP database by removing nonexistent binaries and optimizing. Overrides PROFILE, \-\-hard and \-\-dry
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
[\fIPROFILE\fR]
Run a profile, but refresh its contents. If not defined, all profiles are refreshed, but nothing is run
.TP
[\fIPASSTHROUGH\fR]
Run arguments
